review_blob: Aroma of bread and yeast. Hops are grassy. Appearance very light yellow in color Minimal head, taste is doughy.Palate light body, thin feel, lively, with a long finish. Not a bad beer. Good on a hot day. Taster at Gordon Biersch in Bolingbrook Illinois.

Aroma has alot of Chocolate smells. Appearance dark brown to black in color with sediment on the bottom of the glass. Taste is that of Chocolate with hints of black coffee. Palate soft carbonation, medium body, and a bitter finish. Not the best Chocolate beer I have had.
beer_name: Robinsons Old Tom With Chocolate / Chocolate Tom (Bottle)

review_blob: Aroma. Faint hints of orange with Wet cardboard.Appearance. Hazy yellow color,quickly dissipating head.Taste light sweetness,with medium bitterness.Palate medium body, creamy mouthfeel with very soft carbonation with a slightly bitter finish.

12 oz can. Aroma is all coffee. Appearance is dark brown in color. Taste is coffee with hints of coco. Palate. medium body, sits well on the palate.Overall a awesome tasting coffee brown ale. Will definitely get again.

Aroma. Faint hints of burnt Chocolate. Appearance Black as night with a well kept tan head. Taste. faint chocolate with hints of coffee. Palate medium body, creamy texture with a bitter aftertaste. Overall somewhat impressed. Had it at Goose Island Cybourn. nitro pour.

Aroma. Medicinal with hints of blueberries ,little taste of cardboard. Appearance ruby red. Taste. Blueberries with Robitussin cough medicine. Palate. sits fine on the palate. Overall not thoroughly impressed with this beer. The Cubs would be disappointed in this beer too. Had at Goose Island Cybourn

Aroma on this beer is of coffee, vanilla, and fresh cut flowers. The appearance is bright blonde color,with a quickly dissipating head.The taste has nice coffee notes with medium sweetness. Sat good on the palate with medium body, thin feel, long finish, overall a good collaboration with two very good breweries. This Coffee Blonde Ale is brewed at Upland Brewing Company. Revolution Brewing Company did a Coffee Brown Ale. Both Ales Are Called REVved Up

Citrus Aroma, earthy, has a little bit of banana too. Appearance is flawless with a nice white flothy head fizzing down to beautiful lacing. Taste is medium sourness, with a hint of salt. Palate has fizzy carbonation,medium body, overall not impressed.
Aroma is of bread dough old wet cardboard. Appearance is a typical weizen beer cloudy yellow color.Taste like wet moldy cardboard. Maybe not fresh or light struck. Palate not pleasant.

Aroma smells like banana bread. Appearance is dark yellow in color. Taste like a wet piece of bread.( very chewy beer) palate
light body, with average carbonation, and a long finish of banana bread. Not a good wheat beer.

Aroma is of bread crumbs and bubblegum, with a hint of banana.Appearance is golden in color minimal head very clear beer not hazy. Taste is medium sweetness, very lightly bitter, with lightly sour notes. Palate light body, creamy texture with hardly any carbonation and a very long finish. Taste is better then the Hinterland Saison.

The Aroma is lemon with hints of ground black pepper. Appearance no visible head on this beer dark yellow in color with an unfiltered haze. Taste. Black pepper with lemon zest. No bitterness with this beer. Pepper stays with you well after beer is sipped.medium body. Will try again.
UPDATED: MAR 26, 2016
beer_name: Oskar Blues Deviant Dales India Pale Ale

review_blob: A very sour beer. Not sure of the tastes on this beer I will try this beer again to get an accurate rating for you.

Vintage 2015 8% abv. Tan flothy head that stays with the beer. Nice Belgian lace on the glass. Black in color. Strong smell of bourbon with a hint of oak. Taste is strong bourbon with hints of burnt coffee and wood. Alcohol lingers on the palate. Next time I may try to cellar it for a while to see if the Bourbon mellows a little bit. A good doppelbock
beer_name: Hinterland Out of the Woods Series - Bourbon Barrel Doppelbock: 2015+

review_blob: UPDATED: MAR 26, 2016

Smell of vinegar and berries are present when you crack open this brew. Very acidic on the palate, leaves a funky taste in the mouth. Very cool appearance hazy dark red in color,no visible head on this beer. Overall very instresting brew by off color. Got to get rid of these clear bottles ekk.
beer_name: Off Color Wari: Chicha de mole

review_blob: Alot of Chocolate smells and tastes with this Porter. Malty backbone with hints of Carmel. Very drinkable for a beer being at 8% or 8.5% dangerously drinkable. Nice lacing on the side of the glass. Beautiful tan head that stays with the beer till the end sip. Sits really well on the palate ( no harshness) Appearance is almost black maybe very dark brown in color still has that beautiful lacing going on. A very drinkable, maybe too drinkable for a Porter. The only problem its only available in Wisconsin and it comes in a 4 pack of 16 oz cans. Make a 6 pack of 16oz cans for this Porter. 5 stars
Aroma is freshly ground coffee. Appearance is blonde in color. Taste is coffee with a hint of hops. Sits great on the palate not harsh but sits very clean. Just alot of coffee smells with this beer.
beer_name: Odd Side Ales Bean Flicker Coffee Blonde

review_blob: Coffee smell takes over this beer. Taste is coffee too. Little hops are present in this beer. Sits well on the palate with little hop presentation. Black as night with a nice tan head that stays with the beer for a while. Very well developed beer.
beer_name: Alaskan Pilot Series: Double Black IPA

review_blob: Aroma of coffee. Taste is like drinking a coffee. Appearance is an Amber color. Sits on the palate very well. I really like this coffee ale.
A very good sour beer. Perfect balance of tart and sour notes.sits great on the palate. Nice lacing with a small off white head. Like this sour beer alot.
beer_name: New Glarus Thumbprint Series Oud Bruin

review_blob: Aroma. Bourbon smell. Appearance. Hazy amber color with a very quickly disappearing head to beautiful lacing. Taste is oak,bourbon, and smoke wood. Alcohol is present on the palate. Really good beer from the Cheddar Curtain.
beer_name: Hinterland Out of the Woods Series - Grand Cru

review_blob: Very well balanced IPA. Perfect hop balanced with citrus notes. Floral aroma,with a perfect white head. Sits good on the palate. A very tasty ipa. Cant wait to get more of this awesome beer.

Alot of bourbon smell with this beer. Hints of whiskey in the taste. Little to no lacing. Small white head dissipates quickly to a oily slick that sits on top of the beer. Sits good on the palate with little alcohol. Like this beer
Alot of tangerine taste and smells with this ipa. Very hoppy beer. Yellow in color with nice flothy white head. Beautiful lacing on the sides of the glass. A very good beer worth trying again.
beer_name: Green Flash Tangerine Soul Style IPA

review_blob: Aroma of play dough and berries. Appearance is hazy golden color, taste is strawberries and dough. Sits well on the palate.
UPDATED: MAR 26, 2016
Very malty taste. Smell of lemon peels and prairie grass. Sits really well on the palate. Compliments a pub burger perfectly. Wish they would bottle this beer. No hints of oysters in this beer
Really good tasting ale. Black in color with a flothy white head that retains it self. Aroma of Chocolate and coffee beans. Tastes like chocolate coffee beans. Will drink again.

beer_brewer_name: Leinenkugel Brewing Company (Tenth & Blake Beer Co.)
review_blob: Not bad beer. Its only for the Wisconsin region. Red in color nice white head dissipates quickly to a nice lacing show. Very malty taste,little hops on the end. Will get again.

Not the best Saison. Smell is of a farmhouse or barnyard smell of hay with a hint of apricot. 
funky taste of sour apricots with a hint of grass. Will not try again.

Aroma of roasted coffee and chocolate. Black in color with a little tan head with nice little lacing.Taste like a coffee Porter and a chocolate Stout? No alcohol present on the taste. A very tasty stouter (aka Stout/Porter)
One of the best smoked Porters I have ever had. Aroma has a bonfire smoke smell to it. Taste is a chocolate smoke. Sits really well on the palate. All around a awesome smoked Porter

Aroma is blueberry/wine.Taste like Chardonnay or Pinot Grigio with blueberries.Color is ruby red. Sour on the palate with again wine and or blueberries. The blueberries make this beer very sour and tart. Really good beer.

Coffee lovers rejoice. Aroma of freshly brewed strong black coffee. Little to no tan head. Taste is coffee with a hint of alcohol.Sits great on palate with the coffee taste lingering well after the beer is swallowed. Doesnt even taste like a 12.4% beer. Cant wait till next black Friday to see how the coffee stout tastes again. Brewed and stored in Chicago Illinois.
beer_name: Goose Island Bourbon County Stout - Coffee

review_blob: Hints of Cranberries and Orange peels. Ruby red in color with nice lacing on the snifter,no evidence of a head on this beer.The sour hits you towards the end of the sips. Sits well on the palate. Will try again.
beer_name: Dry City Til Your Tarts Content #3

review_blob: Aroma. Smells like fruit loops cereal,wheat smell with fruit. Appearance. Is golden yellow in color. Taste. Fruit loops or fruity pebbles. Overall response. Very pleasant beer with a fruit loops taste.

Alot of tartness with this beer,then hints of melon. Palate. Melon with tartness. Taste. Melon. Appearance. Golden in color with small fizzy white head. Aroma. Smell of melon and wheat. Very tasty. I like this beer alot
Very tasty beer. Has a hint of blackberries and chocolate. Dark color. Tan head fizzles to a thin layer of bubbles. Will buy again.

The aroma smells like vinegar with raspberries. I like the Burgundy color with this beer. Tastes like oak with raspberries. Sits well on the palate, then you get hit with sourness from the raspberries. I like this beer alot, a well brewed beer
Very bland. Hardly a Christmas ale, just a ale. No taste of spices like a Christmas ale should have. Not a good Christmas ale better ones out there
Aroma is of Chardonnay wine and apple. Appearance is light yellow. Taste is dry with hints of Chardonnay and some hops. A very refreshing cider. Sits well on the palate.
beer_name: Pacific Coast DryApple Cider - Chardonnay & Hops

review_blob: UPDATED: NOV 20, 2015

Brewed on 07-01-15 exprires 09-01-16. Not a bad German Weisse beer. Hazy yellow color with a small flothy white head. Citrus tasting,no need for a lemon wedge in the beer( why ruin a good beer anyway). Sits well on the palate.
Nice German beer. Malty taste, hazy Amber color. No head retention on this beer. Very instresting brew.
I cant even describe this beer,but I will try too. Yellow in color white head dissipates quickly. Malty taste with a bite of alcohol. Will try it again.

Got this beer from a good friend. Got it at the brewery. So I think this is as fresh as it can be. Malty taste, hints of chocolate and coffee. Black as night. Tan flothy head stays a while. A very good beer.
A very solid sour beer. Smell of lemons take over this beer. Nice balance with the sour. Very good beer.

Not one of the best sours I have had. Aroma of plums, thinking that the taste would have plums in it, not at all straight sour taste. Sits ok on the palate. Still not the best sours I have had. Bottles on 05-08-15. Still should have been more matured.
beer_name: Uinta Crooked Line Birthday Suit: 22nd Anniversary
